── BANK DATA WAREHOUSE  →  schema prefix: bankdw."TableName" ───────────────
  bankdw.fact_payments     TransactionID, TransactionDate, PayorName,
                           PayorAccountNumber, PayorBank, PayorRoutingNumber,
                           PayeeName, PayeeAccountNumber, PayeeBank,
                           PayeeRoutingNumber, TransactionType, Amount,
                           Currency, Status
    — Central fact table for ALL payment transactions
    — TRANSACTION MODEL: Every transaction has TWO parties:
        • PayorName = the SENDER (company sending money)
        • PayeeName = the RECEIVER (company receiving money)
      Both join to dim_party.PartyName AND salesforce.Account.Name.
      IMPORTANT: When user says "party", "counterparty", "client", or "company"
      in a transaction context, consider BOTH PayorName AND PayeeName unless
      user specifically says "sender"/"payor" or "receiver"/"payee".
      Use: WHERE ("PayorName" ILIKE '%X%' OR "PayeeName" ILIKE '%X%')
    — PayorBank/PayeeBank joins to dim_bank.BankName
    — TransactionType values: 'ACH Credit', 'ACH Debit', 'Wire Transfer',
      'RTP Credit', 'Check Payment', 'ACH Return', 'Wire Return'
    — Status values: 'Completed', 'Pending', 'Failed', 'Returned', 'Reversed'
    — Amount = transaction value in USD

  bankdw.dim_party         PartyKey, PartyID, PartyName, PartyRoleType,
